Now I think I understand what's going on. Let me look at the `initializeNoteEditorDeckSpinner` method more closely. I noticed something in `DeckSpinnerSelection.kt`:

```kotlin
fun initializeNoteEditorDeckSpinner() {
    dropDownDecks = computeDropDownDecks(includeFiltered = false)
    val deckNames = ArrayList<String>(dropDownDecks.size)
    mAllDeckIds = ArrayList(dropDownDecks.size)
    for (d in dropDownDecks) {
        val currentName = d.name
        deckNames.add(currentName)
    }
    val noteDeckAdapter: ArrayAdapter<String?> = object : ArrayAdapter<String?>(context, R.layout.multiline_spinner_item, deckNames as List<String?>) {
        override fun getDropDownView(position: Int, convertView: View?, parent: ViewGroup): View {
            // Cast the drop down items (popup items) as text view
            val tv = super.getDropDownView(position, convertView, parent) as TextView

            // If this item is selected
            if (position == spinner.selectedItemPosition) {
                tv.setBackgroundColor(context.getColor(R.color.note_editor_selected_item_background))
                tv.setTextColor(context.getColor(R.color.note_editor_selected_item_text))
            }

            // Return the modified view
            return tv
        }
    }
    spinner.adapter = noteDeckAdapter
    setSpinnerListener()
}
```

Notice that in this method, `mAllDeckIds` is created but never populated! In the `for` loop, only deck names are added to `deckNames`, but `mAllDeckIds` is never populated.

Let me check if there's a bug there. In the `initializeActionBarDeckSpinner` method:


I see the key difference now. In the action bar spinner initialization, deck IDs are actually being added to `mAllDeckIds`. This suggests a potential oversight in the note editor spinner method, where the deck IDs are not being collected.

The consequence is critical: without populating `mAllDeckIds`, core deck selection and positioning methods will fail. This breaks fundamental navigation and selection logic for decks across the interface.

The bug stems from divergent initialization approaches between action bar and note editor spinner setup, leading to incomplete deck ID tracking.

I'll investigate the `initializeNoteEditorDeckSpinner` method to verify the precise mechanism causing this data population failure.

